content.description:
Start with hands matched on obvious undercling and go straight up using right sidepull and left juggy ledge. Mantle then top out.

Getting set up at the start and finding the right feet for you can be a little tricky. Whether you shoot for the right sidepull first or go straight up with the left will depend on your reach.
content.location: Located on a large boulder by the edge of the water. If hiking south from the main area, this boulder will be on your right.

content.description: While standing in between the two boulders, it starts on the right boulder and goes up on the huecos and pockets straight up.
content.location: On the right boulder just left of hypodermic

content.description: This climb starts on the rock at the base of the right boulder.  Start in a large hueco and go up using pockets to a hold on the lip.  From here, mantle up top out straight up.
content.location: On the right boulder right of the cave and left of feel the rush.

content.description: One the best routes in the lower boulders. Goes up a series of underclings until the upper face hits you.  Commit to the small crimps and carefully float to the top.
content.protection: Preferred to pad the rock that pokes out as well as the main landing below it.
content.location: Located in the middle of the face of the right boulder. Starting holds depends on water level.
